WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:27.914 --> 00:29.547
Whoa! You guys,

00:29.582 --> 00:31.583
this meteor shower's
gonna be incredible!

00:31.618 --> 00:32.684
I'm so excited!

00:32.719 --> 00:34.786
Okay, let's go over
the checklist.

00:34.821 --> 00:36.054
Mirrors?

00:36.089 --> 00:37.355
-Check.
-Directions?

00:37.390 --> 00:39.124
Directions
to Desert Valley, check.

00:39.159 --> 00:40.225
-Snacks?
-Check!

00:40.260 --> 00:42.861
-Ow.
-Seatbelts?

00:42.896 --> 00:44.195
Check!

00:44.230 --> 00:46.431
-Check!
-New driver's license?

00:48.568 --> 00:50.268
-Check.
-You guys all ready to go?

00:50.303 --> 00:52.203
You got the directions
on your phone, right?

00:52.238 --> 00:53.438
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

00:53.473 --> 00:55.640
They can't use a phone
while driving.

00:55.675 --> 00:56.741
It's dangerous!

00:56.776 --> 00:59.444
[ Both conversing in Korean ]

00:59.479 --> 01:01.613
I'm sure
they'll be responsible.

01:01.648 --> 01:03.281
Isn't that right?

01:03.316 --> 01:04.783
Ice Bear is responsible.

01:04.818 --> 01:06.117
[ Ding! ]

01:06.152 --> 01:08.420
-There you go!
-Hmph.

01:08.455 --> 01:10.455
All right, you are the captain
of the van now.

01:10.490 --> 01:13.325
Take care of your crew,
and they will take care of you.

01:13.360 --> 01:16.795
[<i> Lively flute music plays</i> ]

01:16.830 --> 01:18.229
Ice Bear understands.

01:18.264 --> 01:20.332
-Road trip! Road trip!
-Road trip! Road trip!

01:20.367 --> 01:22.400
-Road trip! Road trip!
-Road trip! Road trip!

01:22.435 --> 01:24.569
-Road trip! Road...trip...
-Road trip! Road...trip...

01:24.604 --> 01:26.438
-Road...trip. Road trip.
-Road trip.

01:26.473 --> 01:29.107
-Road trip.
-Trip. Road --

01:29.142 --> 01:30.642
Have fun!

01:30.677 --> 01:31.843
Slow down!

01:31.878 --> 01:35.147
♪♪

01:42.522 --> 01:45.090
[ Laughter ]

01:45.125 --> 01:46.458
-Slug bug!
-Oh.

01:46.493 --> 01:49.127
♪ Sunny day just for two ♪

01:49.162 --> 01:53.031
♪ Think I'll leave my chores
for the morning, hooray ♪

01:53.066 --> 01:54.966
Huh?
- ♪ We'll hang for a few ♪

01:55.001 --> 01:57.369
Boop. Boop. Boop. Boop.
♪ Cause a hullabaloo ♪

01:57.404 --> 02:00.372
♪ This sweaty weather
is no bother ♪

02:00.407 --> 02:02.140
[ Gasps ] Ooh!
♪ Let's fly away ♪

02:02.175 --> 02:05.143
♪ Let's fly away ♪

02:05.178 --> 02:07.679
♪ Let's fly away ♪

02:07.714 --> 02:09.814
[ Snoring ]
♪ So far away ♪

02:09.849 --> 02:11.349
♪ So far away ♪

02:11.384 --> 02:13.518
♪ So far away ♪

02:13.553 --> 02:15.320
Grizz: Uh-oh.
Guys, we have a problem.

02:15.355 --> 02:17.622
We're already out of Star Cakes.
We got to stop to refuel.

02:17.657 --> 02:19.891
And I got to use
- the little panda's room, please.

02:19.926 --> 02:22.360
Ooh!
Let's stop there!

02:22.395 --> 02:24.829
They'll have snacks and
bathroom stuff and dinosaurs!

02:24.864 --> 02:27.499
Ice Bear does not want to make
stops unless emergency.

02:27.534 --> 02:29.300
-Aw, come on!
-I'll only take five minutes!

02:29.335 --> 02:30.702
We have plenty of time
to get to Desert Valley.

02:30.737 --> 02:33.071
It's right there!
- Please, please, please, please?!

02:33.106 --> 02:34.339
-Yay!
-Yay!

02:34.374 --> 02:37.175
-Whoo-hoo! Hooray!
-Yes! Yes!

02:37.210 --> 02:40.445
♪♪

02:43.450 --> 02:46.218
[ Brakes screeching ]

02:53.526 --> 02:55.660
It's the one thing
he's not good at.

02:55.695 --> 02:59.097
[ Brakes screech ]

02:59.132 --> 03:00.398
Huh?

03:00.433 --> 03:02.934
Go get cakes.
- Ice Bear will wait in car.

03:02.969 --> 03:04.369
All right, man, if you say so.

03:04.404 --> 03:07.872
We'll be back
in a jiff!

03:07.907 --> 03:11.109
♪♪

03:16.649 --> 03:18.049
[ Honks horn ]

03:18.084 --> 03:20.251
[ Door opening ]

03:20.286 --> 03:21.886
Oh, sweet relief.

03:21.921 --> 03:24.255
I think I can make it
a whole two hours now.

03:24.290 --> 03:27.125
Where's older brother?

03:27.160 --> 03:29.360
I found you!

03:29.395 --> 03:31.463
Ooh, this is a pretty car.

03:31.498 --> 03:34.566
My mom had one,
- but she pushed it down a ravine.

03:34.601 --> 03:35.567
[ Laughs ]

03:35.602 --> 03:37.402
Wyatt! Oh, good.
You found the car.

03:37.437 --> 03:39.237
Hey, guys,
I want you to meet Wyatt.

03:39.272 --> 03:41.072
He got separated
from his motorcycle gang

03:41.107 --> 03:43.942
and needs a ride.

03:43.977 --> 03:45.443
Hmm.

03:45.478 --> 03:47.745
It's true.
I wouldn't lie to y'all.

03:47.780 --> 03:50.048
I'm in a legit
motorcycle gang.

03:50.083 --> 03:52.750
I told him he could hitch a ride
with us. That's cool, right?

03:52.785 --> 03:55.086
Eh, I guess we could make room
for one more?

03:55.121 --> 03:56.454
Yeah, what'll it hurt?

03:56.489 --> 03:58.623
Wyatt not part of plan.
Wyatt not coming.

03:58.658 --> 04:02.127
Oh, okay. It's just
I got all these snacks,

04:02.162 --> 04:05.263
and now I got no one
to share 'em with.

04:05.298 --> 04:07.265
[ Gasps ]
Okay, I call a vote.

04:07.300 --> 04:09.467
All that want Wyatt
and his Star Cakes aboard,

04:09.502 --> 04:11.236
-say "aye." Aye!
-Aye!

04:11.271 --> 04:13.671
Aye!
- Welcome to the crew, Wyatt!

04:13.706 --> 04:15.607
[ Sighs ]

04:15.642 --> 04:17.809
Wyatt: Everyone was pretty happy
and stuff.

04:17.844 --> 04:19.677
And then I said,
"If y'all come back,

04:19.712 --> 04:21.446
I'll feed you to my tarantula."

04:21.481 --> 04:23.748
And that's how I got rid
of those kitty cats.

04:23.783 --> 04:24.782
-No way!
-Oh, wow.

04:24.817 --> 04:25.917
Wyatt, that's so cool!

04:25.952 --> 04:27.952
-Oh, that's amazing.
-Please, please, please!

04:27.987 --> 04:30.121
[ Cellphone beeping ]

04:30.156 --> 04:32.524
Huh? Oh, no!
- The phone's on low battery!

04:32.559 --> 04:34.659
-You didn't bring the charger?
-I forgot it.

04:34.694 --> 04:37.128
Without directions, we'll get
lost in the desert forever!

04:37.163 --> 04:38.429
Ice Bear will pull over
and buy map.

04:38.464 --> 04:39.797
Don't worry, gang.

04:39.832 --> 04:42.100
I keep a spare charger
in my boot.

04:42.135 --> 04:43.268
Wyatt, you saved us!

04:43.303 --> 04:44.536
You're the best, Wyatt!

04:44.571 --> 04:46.271
Wyatt, you're so prepared
for trips,

04:46.306 --> 04:47.705
maybe you
should be captain!

04:47.740 --> 04:49.307
Oh, stop it!

04:49.342 --> 04:51.509
It's nothing at all, really.

04:51.544 --> 04:53.878
Hmph.

04:53.913 --> 04:55.347
[<i> Giggles</i> ]

04:57.483 --> 04:59.817
I say this calls
- for a special celebration.

04:59.852 --> 05:02.153
Who wants to watch me eat like
six of these cakes at once?

05:02.188 --> 05:03.721
-Oh, man!
-Go for it, Grizz!

05:03.756 --> 05:06.224
-Remember, use napkin.
-Don't worry, I'll be careful.

05:06.259 --> 05:07.892
No, use napkin.

05:07.927 --> 05:09.294
[ Tires screech ]

05:09.329 --> 05:11.396
♪♪

05:11.431 --> 05:13.498
Peek-a-boo!
[ Giggles ]

05:13.533 --> 05:15.833
All right,
so, we'll wash the car.

05:15.868 --> 05:18.703
You go clean up, okay?

05:18.738 --> 05:21.673
[ Water running ]

05:21.708 --> 05:24.442
[ Humming ]

05:28.381 --> 05:30.148
[ Sighs ]

05:30.183 --> 05:33.418
[ Continues humming ]

05:33.453 --> 05:36.721
Oh, look at all this
bathroom graffiti.

05:36.756 --> 05:38.389
[ Chuckles ]

05:38.424 --> 05:41.693
♪♪

05:50.303 --> 05:52.437
[ Groans ]
This is really boring.

05:52.472 --> 05:54.439
You got any music, Wyatt?

05:54.474 --> 05:56.574
Wyatt!
Where'd Wyatt go!?

05:56.609 --> 05:59.410
[ Wyatt humming ]
[ Tapping ]

05:59.445 --> 06:02.380
Oh, what? No toilet paper?

06:02.415 --> 06:04.249
-No.
-What?! Please!

06:04.284 --> 06:05.883
Mercy!
O Captain, my Captain,

06:05.918 --> 06:07.552
we need to head back
to get him!

06:07.587 --> 06:09.554
Ice Bear will not say it again.
We came too far.

06:09.589 --> 06:11.723
A captain does not leave
a sailor behind!

06:11.758 --> 06:14.225
Sailor doesn't bring other weird
sailor on captain's ship.

06:14.260 --> 06:16.594
Uh, but this is actually
my mom's ship.

06:16.629 --> 06:18.596
Ice Bear appointed captain
by Chloe's mom.

06:18.631 --> 06:20.431
Ugh. Aye-aye, Captain!

06:20.466 --> 06:22.600
Your wish is our command.

06:22.635 --> 06:24.636
This is just wrong.
[ Bang ]

06:24.671 --> 06:26.070
-Aah!
-What's going on?!

06:26.105 --> 06:29.574
[ Engine clunking ]

06:29.609 --> 06:31.743
[ Chiming ]
Why'd we stop?

06:31.778 --> 06:34.746
Maybe our ship doesn't approve
of our captain's cruelty.

06:34.781 --> 06:37.081
-No, silly, we're out of gas.
-Well, whose job was it

06:37.116 --> 06:39.050
-to put in the gas?
-W-Why you looking at me?

06:39.085 --> 06:41.085
I was busy wiping off
<i>your</i> space goo.

06:41.120 --> 06:44.155
-No, window wiping was my job.
-Wyatt did all the wiping, dude.

06:44.190 --> 06:46.991
[ All arguing indistinctly ]

06:47.026 --> 06:50.895
[ Horn blaring ]

06:50.930 --> 06:52.397
♪♪

06:52.432 --> 06:54.899
Out.

06:54.934 --> 06:57.235
Come on, guys.
- Let's give him some space.

06:57.270 --> 06:58.403
[ Car door shuts ]

06:58.438 --> 06:59.637
Did you see his face?

06:59.672 --> 07:01.940
Mm, I think
we broke him.

07:04.811 --> 07:07.178
H-Hey, little bro,
how you doing?

07:07.213 --> 07:08.680
Uh, uh, okay.
Cool.

07:08.715 --> 07:11.115
[ Muffled ] Uh, I guess
I'll come back later.

07:11.150 --> 07:12.583
Okay. [ Chuckles ]

07:12.618 --> 07:16.487
Um, let us know
if you need anything.

07:16.522 --> 07:18.823
[ Keys jingling ]

07:18.858 --> 07:23.194
♪♪

07:23.229 --> 07:25.497
[ Twinkle! ]

07:27.700 --> 07:29.967
Captain:
- Aw. What's the matter, sailor?

07:30.002 --> 07:33.304
Has this sea of sand
defeated ye already?

07:33.339 --> 07:35.973
Ice Bear tried.
- Everyone made it too difficult.

07:36.008 --> 07:38.976
Aye, the captain's job
is never easy.

07:39.011 --> 07:41.879
And that's why the captain has
the highest wage on the ship.

07:41.914 --> 07:43.381
Ice Bear
doesn't get paid.

07:43.416 --> 07:45.483
Listen, son,
- what I'm trying to tell you

07:45.518 --> 07:48.820
is that a good captain
never gives up on his crew.

07:48.855 --> 07:51.489
Ice Bear...
- not meant to be good captain.

07:51.524 --> 07:53.291
[ Laughs ]

07:53.326 --> 07:55.159
I once thought that way.

07:55.194 --> 07:57.161
But my crew needed me...

07:57.196 --> 07:59.864
just like they need you.

08:01.367 --> 08:03.334
Well, there you go! Look,
I'm pretty sure we're here.

08:03.369 --> 08:06.537
No. You're looking at the map upside down.
Ugh! Game over, man.

08:06.572 --> 08:09.173
[ Vehicle approaches ]

08:09.208 --> 08:11.409
Huh? We're saved!

08:11.444 --> 08:12.910
Hey! Over here!

08:12.945 --> 08:14.512
Dude, we don't even know
who they are.

08:14.547 --> 08:15.680
They could be dangerous.

08:15.715 --> 08:17.682
Oh, nonsense.

08:17.717 --> 08:19.484
Over here! Over here!

08:19.519 --> 08:22.721
♪♪

08:26.392 --> 08:29.193
[ Engine revving ]

08:29.228 --> 08:31.529
Uh...

08:31.564 --> 08:33.431
Mm! Huh?

08:33.466 --> 08:34.532
Stay back.

08:34.567 --> 08:36.735
[ Muffled speaking ]

08:38.938 --> 08:41.906
Uh, say what? We -- We actually
can't hear you.

08:41.941 --> 08:43.441
Oh. Hmm.

08:43.476 --> 08:46.177
Ahh!
I said what's cooking, fellas?

08:46.212 --> 08:47.378
[ Sprong! ]

08:47.413 --> 08:48.379
-Wyatt!
-Wyatt!

08:48.414 --> 08:49.580
[ All laughing, cheering ]

08:49.615 --> 08:51.048
-It's Wyatt!
-We thought we lost you!

08:51.083 --> 08:53.017
-We're so sorry!
-We forgot to fill up gas.

08:53.052 --> 08:54.552
But we ran
out of gas and --

08:54.587 --> 08:56.587
-We're sorry we left you.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

08:56.622 --> 08:58.089
Not all at once.

08:58.124 --> 09:02.427
Let's hear what happened
from the captain of the ship.

09:02.462 --> 09:04.562
Ice Bear ran out of gas.

09:04.597 --> 09:06.364
Ice Bear...

09:06.399 --> 09:07.598
failed his crew.

09:07.633 --> 09:11.402
Oh, what?
Nobody failed nobody.

09:11.437 --> 09:13.204
We can get you some gas.

09:13.239 --> 09:14.605
Oh, Wyatt, really?!

09:14.640 --> 09:19.277
Yeah, of course,
- if it's okay with the captain.

09:19.312 --> 09:21.078
Ice Bear...

09:21.113 --> 09:23.214
would be grateful.

09:23.249 --> 09:26.284
♪♪

09:34.794 --> 09:38.463
Oh, oh!
Look! There's a spot!

09:38.498 --> 09:40.231
[ Brakes screech ]

09:40.266 --> 09:43.935
Looks like you're gonna
have to parallel park.

09:43.970 --> 09:45.937
O Captain,
my Captain.

09:45.972 --> 09:48.005
Yeah, you can
do this, man!

09:48.040 --> 09:50.608
Take us home, Cap'n.

09:50.643 --> 09:52.443
Ice Bear
won't disappoint.

09:52.478 --> 09:55.713
♪♪

09:59.952 --> 10:01.452
-Yeah! [ Laughs ]
-Whoo-hoo!

10:01.487 --> 10:03.254
-We did it!
-We made it!

10:03.289 --> 10:07.425
-Whoa! Look at that!
-[ Breathing heavily ]

10:07.460 --> 10:09.994
Hey, you know,
I just wanted to say

10:10.029 --> 10:14.465
that I've never seen
a finer docking job in my life.

10:14.500 --> 10:17.702
♪♪

10:26.646 --> 10:28.679
Whoo!
I just saw two!

10:28.714 --> 10:30.648
I'm gonna make
two wishes.

10:30.683 --> 10:31.716
What'd you wish for?

10:31.751 --> 10:34.685
I wish
to never get lost again.

10:34.720 --> 10:36.687
And I wish for more wishes,
of course.

10:36.722 --> 10:38.389
[ Giggles ]
I'm no fool!

10:38.424 --> 10:39.490
[ Chuckles ]

10:39.525 --> 10:41.192
Oh, so beautiful!

10:41.227 --> 10:42.326
Ahh!

10:42.361 --> 10:44.195
Yep. So worth it.

10:44.230 --> 10:46.130
Thanks for driving,
little bro --

10:46.165 --> 10:48.666
I mean Captain.

10:48.701 --> 10:52.036
Anytime.

10:52.071 --> 10:54.739
[ Laughs ]

10:58.744 --> 11:00.177
Dude, what are
you doing?

11:00.212 --> 11:02.180
Uh, nothing.

11:03.716 --> 11:06.718
♪♪

11:16.429 --> 11:17.929
Done!
- Done!           Done!
